/given-names></name><name><surname>Afolayan</surname><given-names>S.</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Using a proforma to improve standards of documentation of an orthopaedic post-take ward round</article-title><source>BMJ Qual. Improv. Rep.</source><volume>2</volume><year>2014</year><fpage>1</fpage><lpage>2</lpage></element-citation></ref><ref id="bib6"><label>6</label><element-citation publication-type="journal" id="sref6"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Thompson</surname><given-names>A.G.</given-names></name><name><surname>Jacob</surname><given-names>K.</given-names></name><name><surname>Fulton</surname><given-names>J.</given-names></name><name><surname>McGavin</surname><given-names>C.R.</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Do post-take ward round proformas improve communication and influence quality of patient care?</article-title><source>Postgrad. Med. J.</source><volume>80</volume><issue>949</issue><year>2004</year><fpage>675</fpage><lpage>676</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">15537856</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="bib7"><label>7</label><mixed-citation publication-type="other" id="sref7">Medical Protection Society. Medical Record Keeping Ireland. 3, 1&#x02013;36. 1-9-2014. London, Medical Protection Society. 10-10-2014. (Ref Type: Online Source)</mixed-citation></ref><ref id="bib8"><label>8</label><element-citation publication-type="journal" id="sref8"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Larimore</surname><given-names>W.L.</given-names></name><name><surname>Jordan</surname><given-names>E.V.</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>SOAP to SNOCAMP: improving the medical record format</article-title><source>J.&#x000a0;Fam. Pract.</source><volume>41</volume><issue>4</issue><year>1995</year><fpage>393</fpage><lpage>398</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">7561714</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="bib9"><label>9</label><element-citation publication-type="other" id="s